items.name: Triss Merigold | The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt
items.description:
Character Lora of Triss Merigold from The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt/ The Witcher 2: Assassins of Kings

"I will not let this become a second Sodden!" -Triss

Redhead is always a win -soul3142


This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International License.

If you want to, you can support me on Patreon or Buy me Coffee.

My Witcher LoRA Index - soul3142's Guide to the Witcher Universe. additionally you can check out some characters i've made from other games also.

Main Trigger Word - trissW3_soul3142 , check examples for other ones.

RECOMMENDATIONS :-

  1. Highres Fix - must, if you are getting blurry and ugly images

    My upscale method: txt2img 512x768 -> send to img2img -> controlnet tile upscale, tile diffusion 2x scale with 4xUltrasharp upscaler and tiled vae

  2. Weight: 0.6 - 0.8

  3. Clip Skip: 2

  4. Denoising - Don't go too high, it can alter a lot of details

  5. For better face's - you can use ADetailer

I use 0.7 weight, 25 steps, Euler a, Clip skip 2 in nearly all my examples with almost same, simple +ve/-ve prompts regardless of checkpoint for my own consistency purposes.

There are imperfections here & there, which i usually leave it in as is, (i never do any inpainting in examples), most of which like hands can be fixed with better prompting, negative embeddings while other like weapons are just bad majority of the time no matter the model as of today.

Some LoRA's are flexible with any clothing, some are not (usually character's with single costume) so keep these things in mind.

This is an unofficial fanmade LoRA, not intended for any commercial purpose and use. All characters and IP rights are owned by their respective creators and owners. I do not own rights to any of these characters.

items.name: Jean-Baptiste Monge Style
items.description:
Jean-Baptiste Monge is a French artist and illustrator known for his captivating fantasy and folklore-themed artwork.

His style can be described as whimsical, enchanting, and rich in detail. Monge's illustrations often depict mythical creatures, fantastical landscapes, and characters from fairy tales and legends.

He has a distinct ability to bring these imaginative worlds to life with his vibrant use of colors and intricate linework. Monge's attention to detail and meticulous rendering create a sense of realism and depth in his illustrations.

His artwork often showcases a strong connection to nature and a reverence for the mystical and magical aspects of storytelling. Monge's illustrations evoke a sense of wonder, inviting viewers to immerse themselves in his enchanting realms.

Jean-Baptiste Monge's art has been featured in books, magazines, and role-playing games, captivating audiences with its evocative and captivating imagery. His work continues to inspire and transport viewers to realms of fantasy and imagination.

items.name: Jean-Baptiste-Simeon Chardin Style
items.description:
Jean-Baptiste-Siméon Chardin was an 18th-century French painter known for his mastery of still life and genre painting.

His style can be described as realistic and intimate, with a focus on capturing the beauty and simplicity of everyday objects and scenes. Chardin's paintings often depicted domestic interiors, kitchen utensils, and humble objects like fruit, flowers, and tableware.

Chardin had a remarkable ability to infuse his subjects with a sense of quiet elegance and a tactile quality, often using subtle variations in color and texture to bring them to life. His attention to detail and his skill in rendering textures, such as fabric, wood, and glass, were highly admired.

His compositions were carefully balanced, often featuring a harmonious arrangement of objects within a limited space. Chardin's use of light was also notable, as he created a soft, diffused glow that added depth and a sense of tranquility to his paintings.

Chardin's art was highly influential during his time and continues to be celebrated for its technical mastery and the timeless beauty of his subject matter. He remains one of the great masters of still life painting.

items.name: Jean Metzinger Style
items.description:
Jean Metzinger was a French painter and art theorist who played a pivotal role in the development of Cubism, one of the most significant art movements of the 20th century.

His style can be described as analytical and geometric, characterized by the deconstruction and fragmentation of forms into multiple perspectives and facets. Metzinger's paintings often depicted still lifes, landscapes, and portraits, showcasing his innovative approach to representing reality.

Metzinger's work in Cubism involved the exploration of space, time, and movement through the use of geometric shapes and overlapping planes. He embraced a more structured and mathematical approach compared to some of his fellow Cubist artists.

His paintings showcased a fascination with the interplay of light and color, often featuring a muted color palette with hints of vibrant hues. Metzinger's use of angular and faceted forms created a sense of dynamism and intellectual depth.

In addition to his contributions as a painter, Metzinger also wrote extensively on art theory, further contributing to the understanding and development of Cubism.

Jean Metzinger's innovative approach and theoretical insights played a significant role in shaping the course of modern art, and his legacy continues to be celebrated and studied today.

items.name: Blade Runner Style (1982)
items.description:
Introducing Blade Runner Style Model: An AI Model Inspired by the 1982 Movie

The Blade Runner Style Model is an AI model specifically developed to capture and replicate the distinctive visual style of the iconic 1982 movie "Blade Runner." Trained over 20 epochs and 5640 steps, this model has been fine-tuned using a carefully curated dataset consisting of 169 screens from the movie itself.

The training process for the Blade Runner Style Model involved selecting a comprehensive set of frames from the movie, encompassing a variety of scenes, lighting conditions, and compositions. These images were chosen to encapsulate the atmospheric essence, futuristic aesthetics, and cyberpunk elements that define the visual identity of "Blade Runner."

Driven by its exposure to the movie's unique visual style, the Blade Runner Style Model has acquired a deep understanding of the film's characteristic elements. It excels at replicating the distinct color grading, lighting techniques, and architectural motifs found in "Blade Runner." The model adeptly captures the film's neon-lit cityscapes, rain-soaked streets, and gritty urban environments, bringing forth the cyberpunk atmosphere that has become synonymous with the movie.

items.name: Mirai (Senran Kagura)
items.description:
LoRA for Mirai from Senran Kagura

The LoRA was trained on 120 images with 10 epochs, 32 dim and 16 alpha. The images were a mix of official/promotional art and fan art.

  • Use "frills", "frilled dress", "frilled sleeves", "black dress", "capelet", "frilled hairband", "frilled hat" and "cat ears" to make her shinobi outfit.

  • Use "sweater vest", "pink sweater vest", "sleeveless", "star print", "pleated skirt" and "blue skirt" to make her casual attire. Add "white thighhighs" if preferred.

  • Although there were hardly any eyepatch-less images of her, you can still try to remove it by either not including it in the prompt, or using it as a negative with weights.

Trained using this guide: https://civitai.com/models/22530

items.name: Starsky's Ford Gran Torino 1974
items.description:
Hi, I need some support because I ran out of colab credits. Thanks! After 155 models, 240 followers, 28K downloads, thanks to the 7 supporters who made it possible.

Starsky & Hutch is an American action television series, which consisted of a 72-minute pilot movie (originally aired as a Movie of the Week entry) and 92 episodes of 50 minutes each. The show starred Paul Michael Glaser and David Soul in the title roles, Starsky and Hutch. It was broadcast from April 1975 (pilot movie) to August 1979 on the ABC network.

Please provide constructive criticism.

You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

Exclusive models are also available on my Patreon.

Prompt : Ford, realistic, natural lighting, post-processing, ultra realistic, highly detailed, very detailed, cinematic, hyper realistic, intricate scenery, sharp, photo by Annie Leibovitz, film, studio lighting, detailed skin, ultra realistic, bokeh, sharp features <lora:Ford:0.8>

Negative prompt: (deformed iris, deformed pupils, semi-realistic, cgi, 3d, render, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, mutated hands and fingers:1.4), (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, amputation

Steps: 90, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 12, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x1024, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Use Ford as trigger.

New process to get better result :

Set a prompt with a low weight (like <lora:Ford:0.4>) and the action/situation you want (even with a lower resolution like 512x768, it'll be faster and avoid duplicate). Send the result of your choice to img2img, set the weight to <lora:Ford:0.8>, set a higher resolution but keep proportion. Enjoy!
